tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or close to normal limits, except for a mildly decreased MCV (suggesting borderline microcytosis) and a markedly elevated platelet distribution width, which may indicate increased platelet size variability. No acute abnormalities are evident; findings may warrant monitoring for early iron deficiency or other causes of microcytosis if clinically indicated.
